               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-127" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-127" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-127" type="surname" value="HAWKES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-127" type="given" value="PHILIP"></interp>PHILIP HAWKES</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at No. 263, High Holborn. On the afternoon of the 11th of Jan., I was in the counting-house in the centre of the shop, and saw the prisoner come into the shop, take up a dressing-glass, put it on his arm, and walk out with it—I directly followed, and took him with it in his hand—I asked what he was going to do with it—he said a gentleman sent him in for it—I directly gave him in charge—it belongs to my brother, Edward Hawkes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CROUCH</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How many yards was the glass from the door? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Seven or eight—a person coming in might see me in the counting-house—he came in deliberately, and walked out very nimbly with it—I never saw him before—he did not appear intoxicated.</p>
